00:10:45.500 --> 00:10:50.310
of those reasons is due to
cultural misunderstandings.

00:10:50.310 --> 00:10:54.500
So that is why in this time and
age being culturally intelligent,

00:10:54.500 --> 00:11:01.530
being culturally aware is a crucial
skill that's no longer a luxury.

00:11:01.530 --> 00:11:06.330
So a lot of culturalists and
sociologists have likened culture

00:11:06.330 --> 00:11:11.980
to either an iceberg or a
hippopotamus underwater.

00:11:11.980 --> 00:11:14.850
Eighty percent of its
mass is hidden,

00:11:14.850 --> 00:11:20.080
it's covered underneath the water,
and culture is exactly like that.

00:11:20.080 --> 00:11:25.870
It's in that hidden part lies
all the foundations, the values,

00:11:25.870 --> 00:11:30.940 position:56%
the beliefs, that drive our
behavior, that make us see the world

00:11:30.940 --> 00:11:36.610
in a certain way and to determine
what is appropriate, what is not,

00:11:36.610 --> 00:11:40.080 position:56%
what is acceptable, and what is not.

00:11:40.080 --> 00:11:44.020
And it is in that part
where culture lies.

00:11:44.020 --> 00:11:48.680
So what does that mean to us?

00:11:49.970 --> 00:11:55.270
The reality of the matter is
that there is no impartial ground

00:11:55.270 --> 00:11:58.190
from which to interpret reality.

00:11:58.190 --> 00:12:08.160
The fact is we see the world
as we are, not as it is.

00:12:08.160 --> 00:12:13.380
Our beliefs our values all of those
things that we carry on the inside

00:12:13.380 --> 00:12:19.090 position:56%
and that are affected by our culture
determine how we see the world,

00:12:19.090 --> 00:12:21.930
how we view what is
right, what is wrong,

00:12:21.930 --> 00:12:24.970
what is appropriate,
and what is not.

00:12:24.970 --> 00:12:28.160
So we think we use the same words.

00:12:28.160 --> 00:12:30.670 position:56%
We think they're universal concepts.

00:12:30.670 --> 00:12:32.060
They mean the same thing.

00:12:32.060 --> 00:12:34.500
What else could they mean?

00:12:34.500 --> 00:12:35.850
Words like.

00:12:35.850 --> 00:12:37.150
I trust you.

00:12:37.150 --> 00:12:39.660
That's pretty clear.

00:12:39.660 --> 00:12:41.890
What else could it mean?

00:12:41.890 --> 00:12:45.750
But if I was from a
specific culture,

00:12:45.750 --> 00:12:51.300
I trust you means I trust
you will do the right thing.

00:12:51.300 --> 00:12:54.010
If I was from another culture,

00:12:54.010 --> 00:12:58.890
I trust you means I trust you
will do the honorable thing.

00:12:58.890 --> 00:13:01.940
And honorable and [inaudible]
are completely different.

00:13:01.940 --> 00:13:05.150
And if I was from another culture,

00:13:05.150 --> 00:13:08.560
I trust you could mean I
trust you will protect me.

00:13:08.560 --> 00:13:12.560
So we say, I trusted
you but you betrayed me.

00:13:12.560 --> 00:13:14.090
What do you mean I betrayed you?

00:13:14.090 --> 00:13:15.580
I did the right thing.

00:13:15.580 --> 00:13:18.550
Yes, but you didn't protect me.

00:13:18.550 --> 00:13:22.350
And that's where clashes happen.

00:13:22.350 --> 00:13:27.360
So we move to a new culture.

00:13:27.360 --> 00:13:29.360
It might be through work.

00:13:29.360 --> 00:13:32.210
It might be even just
a new organization

00:13:32.210 --> 00:13:34.390
within the same country
where you live.

00:13:34.390 --> 00:13:39.430
And we do things just the way
that we have always been used

00:13:39.430 --> 00:13:43.140
to doing it, because we think
that's the only way to do it.

00:13:43.140 --> 00:13:47.720
But then we realize that the
rules of the game are different.

00:13:47.720 --> 00:13:49.390
Things are different.

00:13:49.390 --> 00:13:53.820
And that is what we
call cultural shock,

00:13:53.820 --> 00:13:57.630
and that should never
be underestimated.

00:13:57.630 --> 00:14:00.690
Cultural shock is when
your expectations

00:14:00.690 --> 00:14:05.240
of how things should be clash
with the reality that you face,

00:14:05.240 --> 00:14:08.590
and things as simple as
just opening the window,

00:14:08.590 --> 00:14:11.250
you're used to seeing
greenery all the time

00:14:11.250 --> 00:14:13.530
and then suddenly you're
in a different country.

00:14:13.530 --> 00:14:17.040
You open the window and you
see just desert and sand,

00:14:17.040 --> 00:14:21.780
or people that look different than
you or the food or the weather.

00:14:21.780 --> 00:14:25.860
Never underestimate how
difficult that can be,

00:14:25.860 --> 00:14:28.850
and what kind of stress
that can cause.

00:14:28.850 --> 00:14:32.680
It can cause a lot of stress.

00:14:32.680 --> 00:14:35.010
It can cause people
to actually go even

00:14:35.010 --> 00:14:40.020
into the victim mentality
of I'm well, I'm fine.

00:14:40.020 --> 00:14:41.320
I'm not the problem.

00:14:41.320 --> 00:14:43.710
It's those stupid locals.

00:14:43.710 --> 00:14:46.760
If only they did things that
they were supposed to do.

00:14:46.760 --> 00:14:48.420
Or it's that crooked system.

00:14:48.420 --> 00:14:51.640
If only they did things the way
that it's supposed to happen,

00:14:51.640 --> 00:14:53.840
then everything will be fine.

00:14:53.840 --> 00:14:55.140
I'm all right.

00:14:55.140 --> 00:15:00.750
It can cause too a lot of
tension in the workplace.

00:15:00.750 --> 00:15:05.120
It can cause too a lot of problems
at home, and it can actually lead

00:15:05.120 --> 00:15:07.730 position:56%
to a lot of substance abuse as well.

00:15:07.730 --> 00:15:13.210
So even if you are the what
we call cultural learner,

00:15:13.210 --> 00:15:16.030
an open minded person
and you have a lot

00:15:16.030 --> 00:15:19.120
of other experiences
outside your own culture,

00:15:19.120 --> 00:15:23.410
still prepare yourself well
before you work or move

00:15:23.410 --> 00:15:26.550
to any other culture, and
take care of yourselves.

00:15:26.550 --> 00:15:30.560
Don't underestimate the effect
that that will have on you.

00:15:30.560 --> 00:15:37.500
But moving to a new culture doesn't
mean that I have to shed my skin.

00:15:37.500 --> 00:15:42.790
It doesn't mean that I have
to forget about my own values,

00:15:42.790 --> 00:15:47.330
forget about my own beliefs,
and go native, as they say.

00:15:47.330 --> 00:15:51.710
No. It just means adjusting
the externals,

00:15:51.710 --> 00:15:53.850
just adjusting the behavior.

00:15:53.850 --> 00:15:59.800
But I keep true to my own DNA, to
my own beliefs, and own values.

00:15:59.800 --> 00:16:02.930
And cultural intelligence
is the ability

00:16:02.930 --> 00:16:07.080
to first look take an
honest look inside myself

00:16:07.080 --> 00:16:12.310
to understand my own beliefs,
my own cultural values.

00:16:12.310 --> 00:16:14.530
The reason how I see the glasses

00:16:14.530 --> 00:16:17.520
through which I see the
world and judge the world.

00:16:17.520 --> 00:16:24.570
Only then am I able to
anticipate other people's behavior.

00:16:24.570 --> 00:16:30.370
Correctly interpret that behavior,
and then adjust my own behavior

00:16:30.370 --> 00:16:33.910
to match the culturally
motivated behavior of others.

00:16:33.910 --> 00:16:37.690
And that is being culturally
intelligent.

00:16:37.690 --> 00:16:42.650
Now, a lot of researchers have
come up with many theories,

00:16:42.650 --> 00:16:48.900
and tools that are meant to help
us understand how culture affects

00:16:48.900 --> 00:16:50.910
