00:45:03.670 --> 00:45:07.470
Language. Lost in Translation.

00:45:07.470 --> 00:45:10.720
The Arabic language, just to say

00:45:10.720 --> 00:45:14.150
that very quickly, it
comes in two parts.

00:45:14.150 --> 00:45:16.640
The instructions were
to write this in Arabic,

00:45:16.640 --> 00:45:20.450
and they did exactly that.

00:45:20.450 --> 00:45:22.340 position:56%
The Arabic language is in two parts.

00:45:22.340 --> 00:45:26.990
There's the classical Arabic, and
there's the colloquial Arabic.

00:45:26.990 --> 00:45:30.880
The classical Arabic is the same
Arab language, the same Arabic

00:45:30.880 --> 00:45:34.740
that is spoken across
all 22 Arab countries.

00:45:34.740 --> 00:45:39.080
It's the same Arabic that is
written in books, in newspapers,

00:45:39.080 --> 00:45:40.440
and you will hear it read

00:45:40.440 --> 00:45:44.120
on the television newscast
or the radio newscast.

00:45:44.120 --> 00:45:47.500
That is the same one that's
across all of the Arab world.

00:45:47.500 --> 00:45:51.400
And then there's the colloquial
Arabic, which is different

00:45:51.400 --> 00:45:57.260
in each country, and each country
has its different dialect as well.

00:45:57.260 --> 00:46:00.920
So, but you'll find that, for
example, the GCC countries,

00:46:00.920 --> 00:46:05.370
the Gulf countries
have a similar dialect.

00:46:05.370 --> 00:46:08.800
The Levant, Jordan,
Lebanon, Palestine,

00:46:08.800 --> 00:46:13.270
and Syria have similar dialect.

00:46:13.270 --> 00:46:15.050
Egypt is very distinct.

00:46:15.050 --> 00:46:16.600
Iraq is very distinct.

00:46:16.600 --> 00:46:21.270
And the North African countries
all have a similar dialect as well.

00:46:21.270 --> 00:46:26.150
But each country has
separate accents.

00:46:26.150 --> 00:46:31.210
You can tell the difference between
Kuwait, and [inaudible] and Saudi

00:46:31.210 --> 00:46:35.100
by the accent, and the
certain words that they use.

00:46:35.100 --> 00:46:43.650
The important thing here is if you
think that you can do a campaign

00:46:43.650 --> 00:46:49.390
or issue a press release at
headquarters, here in the US,

00:46:49.390 --> 00:46:53.890
and then send it out for
translation, think again.

00:46:53.890 --> 00:46:57.060
A lot can get messed
up in the translation.

00:46:57.060 --> 00:47:00.490
When I was working with a
British foreign office I worked

00:47:00.490 --> 00:47:03.070
